<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,150,321]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,258,284]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Etymology.</emphasis>
Derived from the name of the genus which means “false lichen”, with reference to the peculiar spine on the hind femur. The gender is masculine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,809,402,428]" box="[151,809,402,428]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
